org.magelan.core
Interface Derivate

All Superinterfaces:
CoreModel, DrawingModel
All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultVariant
public interface Derivate
extends CoreModel

Derivates are meant to provide specific rendering or additional functionality to their parent DrawingModels, but without being independent drawings themselves. Derivates may not only render the parent differently may but also support entities, layers etc. as any other DrawingModels, and process them together with the elements of their parent.

Note that not all DrawingModel classes may be acceptable for use as parent of a Derivate.

Version:
2.0, 05/2004
Author:
Assen Antov
